# React Components (BSI)

## File structure
Each component folder should contain:
- `ComponentName.tsx` — main component
- `ComponentName.types.ts` — TypeScript interfaces (if complex)
- `index.ts` — re-export

## Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes (design tokens via tailwind.config.ts)
- Never hardcode colors — use semantic tokens (`text-brand-primary`, etc.)
- Mobile-first: start with base styles, add `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints

## Accessibility (WCAG AA minimum)
- All interactive elements need `aria-*` attributes where appropriate
- Images need `alt` text
- Color contrast must pass AA
- Keyboard navigation must work

## Performance
- Use `React.memo` for expensive renders
- Lazy load below-fold components
- Prefer server components where possible (Next.js)

## Sports-specific
- Score displays: always show team logos when available
- Live data: include loading and error states
- Timestamps: always America/Chicago timezone
